1
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,961
[Episode 20: His Freedom]

2
00:01:10,725 --> 00:01:12,959
Before the college entrance exam,

3
00:01:12,959 --> 00:01:14,640
my dad...

4
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,840
That man came to my home

5
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:19,360
and swindled all the savings out of my mom.

6
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:21,389
All he left was a pile of debt.

7
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:25,108
After the college entrance exam,
we got together.

8
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:27,394
<i>Do you want to check together?</i>

9
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:30,799
<i>I'll get going then.</i>

10
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:31,857
<i>Okay.</i>

11
00:01:32,440 --> 00:01:34,094
<i>- Bye.
- Bye.</i>

12
00:01:38,519 --> 00:01:40,701
<i>Inform me when you know it.</i>

13
00:01:42,506 --> 00:01:44,520
The results hadn't been announced.

14
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:48,205
I was worried about
the tuition at Mancheng University.

15
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,239
But because of that,

16
00:01:52,239 --> 00:01:53,640
I didn't perform well.

17
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:56,400
I wasn't admitted to even
a third-tier undergraduate institution.‌

18
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:58,160
I thought, well,

19
00:01:58,160 --> 00:02:00,250
I could find a job and pay off debts.

20
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:04,968
I was a delivery woman,

21
00:02:04,968 --> 00:02:06,320
package sorter,

22
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:07,664
cleaner,

23
00:02:07,664 --> 00:02:09,199
goods loader,

24
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,960
customer server,

25
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,484
everything.

26
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,240
I lived in an urban village.

27
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,991
The monthly rent was 450 yuan.

28
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:19,757
My room was pitifully small.

29
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,479
I remember once

30
00:02:23,479 --> 00:02:25,404
I was scolded harshly by my leader.

31
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:27,919
When I got home, I wanted to hang myself.

32
00:02:27,919 --> 00:02:30,640
But there wasn't enough legroom.

33
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:32,840
The ceiling was within arm's reach.

34
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,880
Rather than a ceiling,

35
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:37,003
it was a plank serving as a partition.

36
00:02:37,003 --> 00:02:38,360
<i>It's been a fortnight.</i>

37
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,673
<i>When will the light be fixed?</i>

38
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:44,649
<i>Please do it soon!</i>

39
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:49,840
I wanted a washing machine,

40
00:02:50,479 --> 00:02:52,960
a balcony to hang my clothes,

41
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:54,919
a room without cockroaches,

42
00:02:54,919 --> 00:02:55,960
money,

43
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,560
a good job,

44
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,680
and a more decent life.

45
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,840
So I got an adult undergraduate degree,

46
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,528
and a new job.

47
00:03:05,599 --> 00:03:07,120
But however hard I tried,

48
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,919
I couldn't get a promotion.

49
00:03:08,919 --> 00:03:10,080
<i>Congrats to Zhang Zheng</i>

50
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,919
<i>for winning the Best Employee Award</i>

51
00:03:11,919 --> 00:03:13,787
<i>and being promoted to Lobby Manager.</i>

52
00:03:13,787 --> 00:03:14,800
<i>Applause!</i>

53
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:17,511
It was the fourth year since high school.

54
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,400
You said you saved money,

55
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,373
and wanted to attend my graduation abroad

56
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,659
after four years of separation.

57
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:29,180
But there was no graduation.

58
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,640
<i>Don't come.</i>

59
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,120
<i>I'll be busy that day.</i>

60
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,680
<i>I won't have time for you.</i>

61
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,479
<i>After that, we'll have club events,</i>

62
00:03:38,479 --> 00:03:40,364
<i>and a road trip</i>

63
00:03:42,719 --> 00:03:44,303
<i>from...</i>

64
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:49,199
<i>Chicago, westwards via Illinois,</i>

65
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:51,369
<i>all the way to California.</i>

66
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,288
<i>I have an appointment with them.</i>

67
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,937
<i>Let's meet after I return. Bye.</i>

68
00:03:59,937 --> 00:04:02,120
The graduation was a lie.

69
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,879
The mailing address was a lie.

70
00:04:03,879 --> 00:04:05,199
The road trip was a lie.

71
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:06,936
But Xiang Nan Feng,

72
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,431
in the world I built with lies,

73
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:14,240
you were the only real thing.

74
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:16,433
<i>I forgot to tell you</i>

75
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,766
<i>that I'm not returning.</i>

76
00:04:19,879 --> 00:04:22,000
<i>I got an offer.</i>

77
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,931
<i>I plan to work here.</i>

78
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:26,024
<i>So...</i>

79
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,326
<i>let's break up.</i>

80
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:37,319
Your sincerity is like a mirror,

81
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:39,818
which reflects my hideousness.

82
00:04:43,839 --> 00:04:45,480
I can lie to anyone else,

83
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:47,870
but not you.

84
00:04:59,759 --> 00:05:02,122
I was too busy

85
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:05,079
and tired to talk with you

86
00:05:05,079 --> 00:05:07,032
over the phone or text.

87
00:05:08,392 --> 00:05:11,680
As for letters,
I didn't know until you mentioned.

88
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:14,131
Our reunion was a coincidence.

89
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:17,400
I don't expect you to forgive me. But I hope...

90
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,960
Hope I can forgive you, right?

91
00:05:23,399 --> 00:05:25,000
Then why did you say

92
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,360
"don't expect"?

93
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,360
How many lies are you going to tell

94
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:31,122
before you let me go?

95
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,360
I intended be honest with you,

96
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,639
and apologize to you.

97
00:05:36,639 --> 00:05:38,400
I do...

98
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:41,440
I do expect your forgiveness.

99
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:43,680
But it's your freedom.

100
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,399
You're honest,

101
00:05:45,399 --> 00:05:47,639
only because you fear

102
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:49,719
you can't go on with your lies.

103
00:05:54,759 --> 00:05:56,215
Xiang Nan Feng!

104
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:05,276
For so many years,

105
00:06:05,879 --> 00:06:08,627
my mood has been at your mercy.

106
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:13,449
It's time to release it.

107
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,709
Only your...

108
00:06:18,079 --> 00:06:19,827
mood?

109
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,701
And my freedom.

110
00:07:49,279 --> 00:07:50,652
Absent-minded?

111
00:07:50,652 --> 00:07:52,760
- I'll clean it up.
- She went to the restroom.

112
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:54,293
She hasn't finished.

113
00:07:54,872 --> 00:07:56,790
Oh. Okay.

114
00:07:58,759 --> 00:08:01,248
You've worked hard recently.

115
00:08:01,248 --> 00:08:03,240
Take a few days off and get refreshed.

116
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,519
What about the diner?

117
00:08:04,519 --> 00:08:06,000
I can hire someone.

118
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,090
You're so distracted. How can you work?

119
00:08:08,090 --> 00:08:10,320
Don't stare at me. Eat some yourself.

120
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,336
You make me feel uncomfortable.

121
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:14,971
Eat more.

122
00:08:16,008 --> 00:08:18,872
Auntie Qiu told me
you wanted a divorce by agreement.

123
00:08:19,825 --> 00:08:21,720
I know you don't want to trouble me.

124
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:24,800
But if you can't handle it, tell me.

125
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,099
I know.

126
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,746
How have you been...

127
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:48,293
Get to the point.

128
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:51,072
You're hungry?

129
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:54,559
I'm... on a diet.

130
00:08:54,559 --> 00:08:56,228
It's a cheat day.

131
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:15,279
You two can go separate ways from now on.

132
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:17,053
Isn't that settled?

133
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:21,560
Why do I feel like it's not?

134
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,440
That's the problem.

135
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,840
You don't want to part ways with him.

136
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:29,360
You still want to be entangled with him.

137
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,925
That's...

138
00:09:31,639 --> 00:09:33,610
I just don't want to be hated.

139
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:37,000
You just want his forgiveness?

140
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,140
Yes.

141
00:09:39,543 --> 00:09:41,200
So my book is useless?

142
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,400
[How to Conquer Handsome Boys]

143
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,519
Since you've brought it,

144
00:09:44,519 --> 00:09:46,399
I'd use it for reference.

145
00:09:46,399 --> 00:09:47,759
I can lend you the book,

146
00:09:47,759 --> 00:09:49,559
but not for free.

147
00:09:49,559 --> 00:09:51,600
I've been too lazy to cook lately.

148
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,282
Can I eat in your place?

149
00:09:53,879 --> 00:09:55,919
You... can.

150
00:09:55,919 --> 00:09:57,480
Good!

151
00:09:57,480 --> 00:10:00,840
From now on, I'm your advisor.

152
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:05,710
Men are easy to handle.

153
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:11,559
Certainly unforgivable.

154
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,541
Any cigarette?

155
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:21,814
No. You should quit.

156
00:10:21,814 --> 00:10:23,049
It's addictive.

157
00:10:26,399 --> 00:10:28,581
Shouldn't start at all.

158
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,865
Your pal's ex confessed and regretted it.

159
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:39,293
Isn't it a success?

160
00:10:42,639 --> 00:10:44,120
If he tries to get back together,

161
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:46,180
you should stop him.

162
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,565
Why isn't Qiao Fei here today?

163
00:11:06,946 --> 00:11:08,624
Thank you for your hard work.

164
00:11:08,624 --> 00:11:10,159
Thank you, Auntie.

165
00:11:10,159 --> 00:11:11,720
You work, I pay.

166
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:14,000
It's justified. Don't mention it.

167
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,200
Where's Xi Zhou?

168
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:17,111
No idea.

169
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,134
Irrigate it.

170
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,512
Here. Yes.

171
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:05,076
Put it there.

172
00:12:14,639 --> 00:12:16,800
It's been days. Will it work?

173
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:19,075
Haste makes waste.

174
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:27,957
He's coming.

175
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,440
Ren Xi Zhou,

176
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:38,679
take back your belongings.

177
00:12:38,679 --> 00:12:40,465
Don't make me repeat.

178
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,350
Go!

179
00:12:57,559 --> 00:12:59,480
There are words inside.

180
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,894
The seaweed sticks.

181
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,920
[Sorry]
